DETECTIVES are hunting a driver who reversed a 4x4 into a pub and then fled the scene.
 Police were called to BJ's Bar on Crow Road, Anniesland, Glasgow shortly before 6.30am. 
 Officers found the front half of a black Jeep Cherokee protruding from the popular pub. 
It had ploughed through a window and was surrounded by shattered glass.
The scene was taped off this morning but pictures of the bizarre crash have been posted on Twitter.
 A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: “The driver made off prior to police arrival 
“Inquiries are ongoing to trace him.”
The force was unable to confirm if the Jeep was stolen.
Officers are examining CCTV footage and speaking to local residents.
Anyone with information is asked to contact the non-emergency 101 number.

